<h2>Cross-platform Shell Reference</h2>
<li>Use <code>&#x26;&#x26;</code> to run commands in sequence. If a command fails, the script exits.</li>
<li>Use <code>|</code> to pipe the stdout of one command into the stdin of the next. (<code>do-something | something else</code>)</li>
<li>Use <code>></code> to write the stdout of a command to a file. (<code>do-something > file</code>)</li>
<li>Use <code>&#x3C;</code> to send the contents of a file to a command's stdin. (<code>command &#x3C; file</code>)</li>
<li>Use <code>cd &#x3C;dir></code> to change the current working directory to <code>&#x3C;dir></code>. Note that <code>cd</code> alone prints the current working directory on windows, but changes the working directory to <code>~</code> on *nix.</li>
